Repeat: P2, (keeping yarn in back, insert right-hand needle from front to back between 4th and 5th stitch on left-hand needle and draw up a loop; k4, then slip the top thread of loop over the 4 stitches)

Begin Row: K1, (keeping yarn in back, insert right-hand needle from front to back between 2nd and 3rd stitch on left-hand needle and draw up a loop; k2, then slip the top thread of loop over the 2 stitches)*
Repeat: p2, (keeping yarn in back, insert right-hand needle from front to back between 2nd and 3rd stitch on left-hand needle and draw up a loop; k2, then slip the top thread of loop over the 2 stitches)
End Row: p2, (keeping yarn in back, insert right-hand needle from front to back between 2nd and 3rd stitch on left-hand needle and draw up a loop; k2, then slip the top thread of loop over the 2 stitches), k1
